      <h2>Physical Therapy Management</h2>
      <p>
        Physical therapy often plays a major role in herniated disc recovery.
        Involving below key points:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Ambulation and resumption of exercise</li>
        <li>Pain control</li>
        <li>Education re maintaining healthy weight</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Physical therapy programmes are often recommended for the treatment of
        pain and restoration of functional and neurological deficits associated
        with symptomatic disc herniation.
      </p>
    </div>
