      <p>
        A herniated disk, which can occur in any part of the spine, can irritate
        a nearby nerve. Depending on where the herniated disk is, it can result
        in pain, numbness or weakness in an arm or leg.
      </p>
      <p>
        Many people have no symptoms from a herniated disk. Surgery is usually
        not necessary to relieve the problem.
